    descriptionEN:
      "Many modifications were made to the roads in 1920 AD, making them popular destinations for tourists who love adventure and mountain climbing.Given the nature of the climate there, where the temperature does not exceed 20 degrees Celsius, and the extreme fertility of the soil, this attracted the attention of a young British man named Jason R. Russell.He was the owner of the first idea to convert the lands into tea plantations, and as a result, in 1929 AD, the trees that were present in the area were cut down and converted into tea plantations, in addition to other places where vegetables, fruits, and flowers were grown.",
